==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plenitude
<hw>Plen"i*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>plenitudo</ets>, fr. <ets>plenus</ets> full; cf. F.
<ets>plenitude</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of
being full or complete; fullness; completeness; abundance; <as>as, the
<ex>plenitude</ex> of space or power</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Animal fullness; repletion; plethora.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plenitudinarian</ent>⟦br⟧
